<br>
1.  I currently use Queen's Carapace which is very nice.<br>
<br>
2.  I don't have any invis items currently.<br>
<br>
3.  Legs I use now are Blood Runed.<br>
<br>
Please help me make mah decision, or should I scratch both and buy a Fleshgrinder? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubludar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bludar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/02 7:54:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4058.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Cobalt BP or Cobalt Leggs?</span><hr size=1> Have you considered cultural BP and legs?  You could probably afford both (approx 30k each on Tunare) and have some nice pp left over if you sell current legs and bp.<br>
<br>
Something that may be worth checking into.  You could buy a lot of invis potions with that kind of change <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Friedrick - 59th Myrmidom on Tunare server<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugriglon1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Griglon1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/02 7:56:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4058.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Cobalt BP or Cobalt Leggs?</span><hr size=1> I would go with the legs personally.  The invis is one of the best effects to have on a piece of armor.  Especially since you can cast it on others as well.  Any of the velious quest BP have close to or more than the AC of the cobalt with the same effect.  Also, the cobalt legs have very good AC and stats to go with the effect.  Just my 2 cp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufoolsfizzelmore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fools Fizzelmore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/02 7:57:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4058.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   bp or legs</span><hr size=1> buy neither.<br>
<br>
PoP around the corner. Save your cash. No idea what kind of new legs/bps are to be had.<br>
<br>
not to mention the fact that you can get quest armor or pog armor. <br>
<br>
70k a piece is too much to spend on those peices in my opinion. If you are RZ...then cultural is a FAR better choice....and cheaper too. (but minus the effects of course)<br>
<br>
<br>
cuch <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umahheritage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mahheritage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/02 8:15:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4058.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: bp or legs</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the suggestions.  Me no follow anything so can't get cultural armor <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udaxanu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daxanu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/02 9:46:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4058.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: bp or legs</span><hr size=1> Actually, you can get Helanic Tundra armor if anyone is making it on your server (which I have found rather rare, noobdy seems to make it).  Helanic Tundra, if I remember correctly, is the same +HP properties of Fierce Heraldic, and is not diety limited... though it is race limited.<br>
<br>
WAR/BRD<br>
Medium Race classes I believe... Barbarian IS included though.<br>
<br>
Definitly one of the best options for +HP gear if you are Barbarian/Human/Medium race warrior.<br>
<br>
About your question on the Cobalt BP or Legs, I would go Legs.  The BP is absolutely a nice look, but you can MQ a Thurg BP easy (at least on my server, as they are common).  I have a full set of Cobalt, and I use the cobalt legs every day, multiple times.  One of the best single piece of armor/item that I've ever owned.  <br>
<br>
Sure there are multiple choices now that will perhaps give you a better AC or HP or Stat ratio but the effect, to me, is the single best effect I have.<br>
<br>
No more carrying a full bag of invis potions...no more using up the last charge on my Larikan's mask and having to either fight for another or buy one.  I just click the pants and move on.<br>
<br>
Nice side effect is that cleric's will love you for it when you dont have anyone else who can do it in a small group. <p><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=62401">Valthar</a></b> - 60 Warrior
<br>
<b>Daxanu</b> - 53 Druid
