ymore, they have retained their value very well. (since there are so few warrior usable invis items) So, you won't lose much, if anything, by selling them later. <p><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5309"target="_blank"alt = "Korak's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 10,10,900><b>Korak Sarathai - Barbarian Warlord - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12530"target="_blank"alt = "Dumesh's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 900,10,10><b>Dumesh Uhl'Belk - Retired Troll Reaver - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usplaktar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Splaktar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 329<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/4/02 10:41:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4058.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: bp or legs</span><hr size=1> Cobalt Legs for sure. <p><a href="http://www.akanon.org/view_profile.php?num=12">Gurgel Troll Warlord</a><br>
